{
  "doc_id": "15369",
  "text": "Over the years, several vaccine targets and vaccination routes have been proposed and tested [CITATION_1] . Some of them have shown great potential in protecting animals against leishmaniasis (2). Remarkably few have been able to proceed to a clinical trial. This lack of progress is partly due to lack of a small-animal model that reflects human disease, and to the fact that many vaccines are tested with cutaneous strains where the testing has been undertaken by injections instead of sand fly bites [CITATION_2] .",
